spanishExample: Nunca juegan conmigo, así que jugué solo.
englishTranslation: They never play with me, so I played alone.
vocabIncluded: juegan: play, they play (Jugar, present, 3rd person plural)
jugué: played, I played (Jugar, preterite, 1st person)

spanishExample: Ella quiere que yo la ayude con su cita.
englishTranslation: She wants me to help her with her date.
vocabIncluded: "que", meaning "that" as a conjunction (even in cases where "that" disappears in English)
ayude: help, I help (Ayudar, subjunctive, 1st person)

spanishExample: ¡Ayúdame! Solo tengo cuarenta respuestas y necesito cincuenta.
englishTranslation: Help me! I only have forty answers and I need fifty.
vocabIncluded: necesito: need, I need (Necesitar, present, 1st person)

spanishExample: No juegues con ella si ella no juega con él.
englishTranslation: Don’t play with her if she doesn’t play with him.
vocabIncluded: juega: plays , he/she/it plays (Jugar, present, 3rd person)

spanishExample: Disculpe, estamos jugando aquí ahora.
englishTranslation: (Formal) Excuse me, we are playing here now.

spanishExample: Disculpa, no sabes cuánto ha significado esto para mí.
englishTranslation: Excuse me, you don’t know how much this has meant to me.
vocabIncluded: cuánto: adverb meaning "how much?" in a question or implied question
ha: "has", "he/she/it has" before a participle (Haber, present, 3rd person)

spanishExample: Eso significaba que yo nunca jugaba.
englishTranslation: That meant that I never played.
vocabIncluded: "que", meaning "that" as a conjunction (even in cases where "that" disappears in English)
jugaba: played, I played (Jugar, imperfect, 1st person)
significaba: meant, he/she/it meant (Significar, imperfect, 3rd person)

spanishExample: Los padres de hoy en día no quieren que sus hijos jueguen afuera.
englishTranslation: The parents nowadays don’t want their kids to play outside.
vocabIncluded: "que", meaning "that" as a conjunction (even in cases where "that" disappears in English)
de hoy en día: of today/of these days (idiom)
jueguen: play, they play (, subjunctive, 3rd person plural)

spanishExample: Eso podría significar que vas a disculparme.
englishTranslation: That could mean that you’re going to forgive me.
vocabIncluded: "que", meaning "that" as a conjunction (even in cases where "that" disappears in English)
disculparme: to forgive me (Disculpar infinitive) + CONTRACTION
podría: "would be able", "he/she/it would be able" (Poder, conditional, 3rd person)
using Ir and "a" to put verbs in the future (e.g. "voy a ser")

spanishExample: Puedo ayudarte después de ver las noticias.
englishTranslation: I can help you after watching the news.
vocabIncluded: ayudarte: to help you (Ayudar infinitive) + CONTRACTION

spanishExample: Necesito una señal para tomar una decisión, alguien me tiene que ayudar.
englishTranslation: I need a signal to make a decision, someone has to help me.
vocabIncluded: necesito: need, I need (Necesitar, present, 1st person)
para: "in order", "in order to" before an infinitive
using Tener with "que" to indicate obligation

spanishExample: Si juegas con ellos, quizás te disculpen.
englishTranslation: If you play with them, maybe they’ll forgive you.
vocabIncluded: disculpen: forgive/excuse, they forgive/excuse (Disculpar, subjunctive, 3rd person plural)
juegas: play, you play (Jugar, present, 2nd person)

spanishExample: Mi hijo jugó con mi hija en Navidad.
englishTranslation: My son played with my daughter on Christmas.
vocabIncluded: jugó: played, he/she/it played (Jugar, preterite, 3rd person)

spanishExample: No tienes que ayudarme, puedes jugar.
englishTranslation: You don’t have to help me, you can play.
vocabIncluded: ayudarme: to help me(Ayudar infinitive) + CONTRACTION
using Tener with "que" to indicate obligation

spanishExample: Discúlpame, no sabía que era tu cumpleaños.
englishTranslation: Forgive me, I didn’t know it was your birthday.
vocabIncluded: "que", meaning "that" as a conjunction (even in cases where "that" disappears in English)

spanishExample: ¡Juguemos a la prueba de este juego!
englishTranslation: Let’s play this game’s demo!
vocabIncluded: a: complement (e.g. ayudar a, empezar a) (preposition)

spanishExample: Quizás no te ayude porque no sabe el porqué.
englishTranslation: Maybe she won’t help you because she doesn’t know the reason.
vocabIncluded: ayude: help, he/she/it help (Ayudar, subjunctive, 3rd person)

spanishExample: Jugamos juntos la semana pasada, pero no sé qué significan esas cosas.
englishTranslation: We played together last week, but I don’t know what those things mean.
vocabIncluded: "qué" in an implied question, not an actual question
jugamos: played, we played (Jugar, preterite, 1st person plural)
significan: mean, they mean (Significar, present, 3rd person plural)

spanishExample: Discúlpeme, pero no necesitaba su consejo.
englishTranslation: (Formal) Excuse me, but I didn’t need your advice.
vocabIncluded: discúlpeme: forgive me / excuse me (Disculpar formal imperative) NEEDS WORK
necesitaba: needed, I needed (Necesitar, imperfect, 1st person)

spanishExample: Disculpa, no jugaba ahí.
englishTranslation: Excuse me, I wasn’t playing there.
vocabIncluded: ahí: adverb meaning "there", especially when close to the speaker or listener
jugaba: played, I played (Jugar, imperfect, 1st person)

spanishExample: Disculpe, ¿quiere que yo juegue?
englishTranslation: (Formal) Excuse me, do you want me to play?
vocabIncluded: "que", meaning "that" as a conjunction (even in cases where "that" disappears in English)
juegue: play, I play (Jugar, subjunctive, 1st person)

spanishExample: Siempre jugamos juntos y por eso ella quiere que yo los disculpe.
englishTranslation: We always play together and that’s why she wants me to forgive them.
vocabIncluded: "que", meaning "that" as a conjunction (even in cases where "that" disappears in English)
disculpe: forgive/excuse, I forgive/excuse (Disculpar, subjunctive, 1st person)
jugamos: play, we play (Jugar, present, 1st person plural)

spanishExample: Discúlpenme, nunca juego así.
englishTranslation: (Plural) Forgive me, I never play like this.
vocabIncluded: así: adverb meaning "this way", "that way", "like this", "like that"
discúlpenme: excuse me / forgive me (Disculpar, plural imperative contraction)

spanishExample: Si te disculpas, puedes ayudarlo.
englishTranslation: If you apologize, you can help him.
vocabIncluded: ayudarlo: to help him (Ayudar infinitive) + CONTRACTION
disculparse: any use of forgive with a reflexive pronoun, changing the meaning to apologize)
disculpas: forgive/excuse, you forgive/excuse (Disculpar, present, 2nd person)

spanishExample: No quiero que juegues con ellos, más bien con él.
englishTranslation: I don’t want you to play with them, rather with him.
vocabIncluded: "que", meaning "that" as a conjunction (even in cases where "that" disappears in English)
juegues: play, you play (Jugar, subjunctive, 2nd person)

spanishExample: No he jugado en un tiempo y eso significa que no sé qué pasará.
englishTranslation: I haven’t played in a while and that means I don’t know what will happen.
vocabIncluded: "que", meaning "that" as a conjunction (even in cases where "that" disappears in English)
"qué" in an implied question, not an actual question
he: "have", "I have" before a participle (Haber, present, 1st person)
pasará: will pass, he/she/it will pass (Pasar, future, 3rd person)
significa: means, he/she/it means (Significar, present, 3rd person)

spanishExample: ¡Ayúdala a hacer esa llamada en el futuro!
englishTranslation: Help her make that call in the future!
vocabIncluded: a: complement (e.g. ayudar a, empezar a) (preposition)

spanishExample: Juega con ella para que nosotros también juguemos.
englishTranslation: Play with her, so that we also play.
vocabIncluded: juguemos: play, we play (Jugar, subjunctive, 1st person plural)

spanishExample: Siempre lo ayuda.
englishTranslation: She always helps him.
vocabIncluded: ayuda: helps, he/she/it helps (Ayudar, present, 3rd person)
